<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n36189d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n36" href="#n36189d">N36 (VI.B.29)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n36all.htm#n36189d"> 189(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Bowery = farm</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">I must not omit to mention that in portioning out the land, a goodly &lsquo;<mark>bowerie</mark>&rsquo; or farm, was allotted to the sage Oloffe &hellip; and the site of his &lsquo;bowerie&rsquo; is known by the name of Kortlandt (or Courtland) street to the present day. <small> Washington Irving, <a name="WINY" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#WINY"><cite title="source">A History of New York, by Diedrich Knickerbocker</cite></a> (ed. unknown) 59</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c09107d" href="c09all.htm#c09107d">VI.C.09:107(d)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
